{
  "texts": [
    "In this study, critical thinking is defined as the ability to evaluate information and arguments rigorously, particularly in the context of using adversarial attacks on LLMs.",
    "In this work, we aim to evaluate GAI responses within chemistry education, emphasizing its limitations and capabilities.",
    "When effectively utilized, LLMs present significant advantages for educational purposes, offering real-time feedback, scalability, and better engagement (van Gelder, 2005).",
    "These attributes have been effectively leveraged across various disciplines, including mathematics and sciences, enhancing the online learning experience significantly.",
    "The modern classroom must elevate critical thinking above all, integrating technology in a manner that complements this goal, rather than compromising it."
  ]
}